      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OUTA THE BLUE (3) is building in fitness and there was plenty to like about the latest effort when beaten 4.7m at Bendigo when off the back row. Better drawn and could peak here. OUR BELLA LUCIA (8) continues a run of second line draws but has been racing well from there, placing two back in SA before a fourth at Ballarat last week. She should enjoy the return to a circuit where she strikes at 50 per cent when racing over this distance. OUR MYSTERY BET (7) eases back in grade on the last two outings. Draws wide but was an easy winner at Shepparton three back. Forget the latest result of NORTHERN TERROR (9) when he was severely checked and broke and instead assess his chances off an easy Shepparton win prior.",
